1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,970
Actually, in these modern times, belief is doing much bigger things than moving mountains.

2
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:16,129
The most essential element—in fact, the essential element—in our space explorations today is belief that space can be mastered.

3
00:00:16,319 --> 00:00:23,730
Without firm, unwavering belief that man can travel in space, our scientists would not have the courage,

4
00:00:23,839 --> 00:00:26,690
interest, and enthusiasm to proceed.

5
00:00:26,959 --> 00:00:32,290
Belief that cancer can be cured will ultimately produce cures for cancer.

6
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:39,250
Currently, there is some talk of building a tunnel under the English Channel to connect England with the continent.

7
00:00:39,519 --> 00:00:45,970
Whether this tunnel is ever built depends on whether responsible people believe it can be built.

8
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:54,690
Belief in great results is the driving force, the power behind all great books, plays, scientific discoveries.

9
00:00:55,040 --> 00:01:01,329
Belief in success is behind every successful business, church, and political organization.

10
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:07,889
Belief in success is the one basic, absolutely essential ingredient of successful people.

11
00:01:08,319 --> 00:01:12,930
Believe, really believe you can succeed, and you will.

12
00:01:13,519 --> 00:01:20,290
Over the years, I've talked with many people who have failed in business ventures and in various careers.

13
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:23,970
I've heard a lot of reasons and excuses for failure.

14
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:30,050
Something especially significant unfolds as conversations with failures develop.

15
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:35,329
In a casual sort of way, the failure drops a remark like, to tell the truth,

16
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:41,250
I didn't think it would work, or I had my misgivings before I even started out,

17
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:45,969
or actually, I wasn't too surprised that it didn't work out.

18
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:53,329
The OK, I'll give it a try, but I don't think it will work attitude produces failures.

19
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:56,449
Disbelief is negative power.

20
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:03,010
When the mind disbelieves or doubts, the mind attracts reasons to support the disbelief.

21
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:13,170
Doubt, disbelief, the subconscious will to fail, the not really wanting to succeed, is responsible for most failures.

22
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,650
Think doubt and fail.

23
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:18,290
Think victory and succeed.

